snippet: The opposition said it would boycott the opening session of Parliament and carry out more street protests, arguing it would have won the election if the vote had been fair.
lead_paragraph: The opposition said it would boycott the opening session of Parliament and carry out more street protests, arguing it would have won the election if the vote had been fair.

headline.main: Election Results Ratified in Cambodia, but Opposition Plans Boycott
headline.print_headline: Election Results Ratified in Cambodia, but Opposition Plans to Boycott Parliament
